# Shopify Customer Password Reset Email Template

## Instructions:
1. Go to Shopify Admin → Settings → Notifications
2. Find "Customer account password reset"
3. Click "Edit code"
4. Replace the ENTIRE email body with this template

## Complete Email Template:

```liquid
{% capture email_title %}Reset your password{% endcapture %}
{% capture email_body %}
Follow this link to reset your customer account password at {{ shop.name }}. If you didn't request a new password, you can safely delete this email.
{% endcapture %}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>{{ email_title }}</title>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <style type="text/css">
      body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
      table { border-collapse: collapse; }
      .button { 
        background-color: #5469d4;
        border-radius: 4px;
        color: #ffffff;
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: sans-serif;
        font-size: 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
        line-height: 50px;
        text-align: center;
        text-decoration: none;
        width: 100%;
        -webkit-text-size-adjust: none;
        mso-hide: all;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
      <tr>
        <td align="center" style="padding: 40px 0;">
          <table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 40px; background-color: #ffffff;">
                <h1 style="margin: 0 0 20px; font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; color: #000000;">{{ shop.name }}</h1>
                <h2 style="margin: 0 0 20px; font-size: 24px; font-weight: normal; color: #000000;">{{ email_title }}</h2>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; color: #666666;">{{ email_body }}</p>
                
                <!-- CUSTOM RESET BUTTON WITH YOUR DOMAIN -->
                <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 20px 0;">
                  <tr>
                    <td>
                      <a href="https://dude.box/portal/reset-password?id={{ customer.id | split: '/' | last }}&token={{ customer.reset_password_url | split: '/' | last }}" class="button" style="background-color: #c79d7a; color: #0f1628; padding: 15px 30px; text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; border-radius: 9999px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em;">
                        Reset your password
                      </a>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
                
                <p style="margin: 20px 0 0; font-size: 14px; color: #999999;">
                  or <a href="{{ shop.url }}" style="color: #5469d4;">Visit our store</a>
                </p>
                
                <hr style="margin: 40px 0; border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eeeeee;">
                
                <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14px; color: #999999;">
                  If you have any questions, reply to this email or contact us at 
                  <a href="mailto:dude@dude.box" style="color: #5469d4;">dude@dude.box</a>
                </p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>
```

## Quick Fix (If You Want to Keep Shopify's Default Template):

If you want to keep Shopify's existing template structure and just change the button URL, find this line:

```liquid
<a href="{{ customer.reset_password_url }}" class="button">Reset your password</a>
```

And replace it with:

```liquid
<a href="https://dude.box/portal/reset-password?id={{ customer.id | split: '/' | last }}&token={{ customer.reset_password_url | split: '/' | last }}" class="button">Reset your password</a>
```

